+## [0.8.0] - 2026-05-29
+
+Backward-compatible feature release. Consolidates the money primitives
+(`round` ┬Ě `arithmetic` ┬Ě `format`) into a single shared **`src/lib/money`
+kernel** and adopts the drift-free, fail-loud `formatMoney` app-wide, so every
+visible balance is provably the canonical stored value. No breaking changes
+since `0.7.0` ÔÇö the old `src/features/ledger/lib/{round,arithmetic,format}`
+entry points are retained as re-export shims for one release ÔÇö so under the
+pre-1.0 `0.x` policy a feature release increments the **minor**, landing as
+`0.8.0`. Bump derived from `git log v0.7.0..HEAD` (one `feat` commit ÔÇö `ea3641d`
+ADR-0005 money-kernel consolidation ÔÇö additive, none breaking), not guessed.
+
+### Added
+
+- **Shared money kernel** (`src/lib/money/`, exported via the `@/lib/money`
+  barrel) ÔÇö `roundMoney`, `addMoney`/`subtractMoney`,
+  `formatMoney`/`formatMoneyCompact` plus currency minor-unit resolution, with
+  co-located round/arithmetic/format test suites. The canonical home for the
+  banker's-rounding, fail-loud money primitives [ADR-0005].
+- **ESLint money-formatting guardrail** ÔÇö feature components are now linted
+  against raw `` $${ÔÇŽ} `` / `.toFixed()` money rendering, forcing all visible
+  balances through the kernel formatter so display can't drift from stored.
+
+### Changed
+
+- `formatCurrency` / `formatSignedCurrency` (`src/lib/format.ts`) re-implemented
+  as thin kernel-backed wrappers ÔÇö the U+2212 minus sign is preserved and
+  golden-string tests were added to pin the output.
+- All 8 money-render surfaces (including the v0.7.0 `LedgerExplorer`, which had
+  wired to the un-normalized formatter) now route through the kernel, realizing
+  ADR-0004's "display == stored" guarantee that previously had 0 consumers.
+- `WealthScoreCard`'s inline `$ÔÇŽM` / `$ÔÇŽK` abbreviator replaced with the kernel
+  `formatMoneyCompact`.
+- `src/features/ledger/lib/{round,arithmetic,format}` reduced to re-export shims
+  pointing at the kernel (kept one release for a clean deprecation window).
+
+### Tests
+
+- **95/95 unit tests pass** (`tsx --test`); golden-string format tests and the
+  full money-kernel suite migrated alongside the kernel.
+
+### Known issues / carry-forward
+
+- **postcss XSS ÔÇö GHSA-qx2v-qp2m-jg93** (moderate) remains open: `next@16.2.6`
+  nests `postcss@8.4.31` (< 8.5.10). Non-blocking (build-time CSS stringify, not
