+# Release v0.8.0 ÔÇö Shared Money Kernel: One Formatter, No Drift
+
+**Date:** 2026-05-29
+**Bump:** MINOR (`0.7.0 Ôćĺ 0.8.0`)
+**Tag:** `v0.8.0` Ôćĺ release commit
+
+## Why this version
+
+Backward-compatible feature release, **no breaking changes** since `0.7.0`.
+Under `0.x` semantic versioning a feature release increments the **minor**, so
+this lands as `0.8.0`. The bump is derived from the merged history, not guessed:
+`git log v0.7.0..HEAD` is a single `feat` commit ÔÇö `ea3641d` (ADR-0005
+money-kernel consolidation) ÔÇö additive, not breaking. The prior per-feature
+`src/features/ledger/lib/{round,arithmetic,format}` entry points are kept as
+re-export shims for one release, so no consumer breaks.
+
+## Headline
+
+The money primitives finally live in **one place**. `round` ┬Ě `arithmetic` ┬Ě
+`format` are promoted to a shared **`src/lib/money`** kernel, and the
+drift-free, fail-loud `formatMoney` is adopted **app-wide** ÔÇö so every visible
+balance is provably the canonical stored value. This closes the gap ADR-0004
+opened but never realized: `formatMoney` previously had **0 real consumers**
+while all 8 money-render surfaces flowed through an un-normalized USD-only path,
+and v0.7.0's new `LedgerExplorer` had wired straight to the wrong formatter,
+proving the drift was still accumulating.
+
+## What's new
+
+- **Shared money kernel** (`src/lib/money/`, via the `@/lib/money` barrel) ÔÇö
+  `roundMoney`, `addMoney`/`subtractMoney`, `formatMoney`/`formatMoneyCompact`,
+  and currency minor-unit resolution, with co-located round/arithmetic/format
+  test suites. The single canonical home for the banker's-rounding, fail-loud
+  money primitives [ADR-0005].
+- **ESLint money-formatting guardrail** ÔÇö feature components are linted against
+  raw `` $${ÔÇŽ} `` / `.toFixed()` money rendering, so visible balances can't
+  bypass the kernel formatter and drift from stored values.
+- **`formatCurrency` / `formatSignedCurrency`** re-implemented as thin
+  kernel-backed wrappers (U+2212 minus preserved; golden-string tests pin the
+  output).
+- **All 8 money-render surfaces** ÔÇö including the v0.7.0 `LedgerExplorer` and
+  `WealthScoreCard`'s inline `$ÔÇŽM`/`$ÔÇŽK` abbreviator (now
+  `formatMoneyCompact`) ÔÇö route through the kernel.
+
+## Quality gate
+
+All four gates green on the release commit:
+
+- `tsc --noEmit` ÔÇö clean
+- `eslint .` ÔÇö clean (including the new money-formatting guardrail rule)
+- `tsx --test` ÔÇö **95/95 pass**
+- `next build` ÔÇö success (8 routes; `/api/categorize` server-rendered on demand)
+
+## Known issues / carry-forward
+
+- **postcss XSS ÔÇö GHSA-qx2v-qp2m-jg93** (moderate) remains open: `next@16.2.6`
+  nests `postcss@8.4.31` (< 8.5.10). Non-blocking (build-time CSS stringify, not
+  user-input-fed). Fix = a one-line `package.json` `overrides` pin
+  (`"postcss": ">=8.5.10"`); do **not** `npm audit fix --force` (it proposes a
+  wrong `next@9.3.3` downgrade).
+- **`CategorizePanel.tsx`** is a fourth un-normalized money-render path left
+  outside ADR-0005's scope ÔÇö ticketed for a later item.
+- The `src/features/ledger/lib/{round,arithmetic,format}` re-export shims are a
+  one-release deprecation window; plan to remove them in a future release.
+
+## Security carry-forward (from the upstream scan @ ea3641d)
+
+The release commit is the same tree the security scan cleared. Standing,
+non-blocking items handed to triage:
+
+- `/api/categorize` (the first app/api route) is **unauthenticated with no rate
+  limiting** in front of paid Gemini calls ÔÇö denial-of-wallet / DoS (Medium).
+- `description` is **unbounded** before the model prompt ÔÇö token-cost
+  amplification + prompt-injection surface (Medium).
+- Model-returned account names are **not validated** against a chart of accounts
+  (Low).
+
+These are tracked separately and were not introduced by this increment; they do
+not block the release.
